The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Wessels faces racism probe
Johannesburg: The UCBSA has instructed Eastern Province to suspend coach Kepler Wessels after he allegedly made racist remarks earlier this year. The board instructed Eastern Province to suspend Wessels on full pay pending the outcome of a disciplinary hearing which will be held shortly regarding allegations of racist remarks, the UCBSA said in a statement. Wessels said: I demand the investigation take place as soon as possible. The matter is in the hands of my legal advisors and we will fight it all the way. I am looking forward to the outcome.  Smith fractures finger Graeme Smith suffered a fracture to the middle finger of his right hand during a provincial match on Monday.  (AGENCIES)  Copyright 
